{
  "stem": "24409.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had told Rajakowicz before that I would give a talk in which I demand and remind them that they have to be very disciplined on the trip.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I started out with saying, you are leaving now a country where you are not wanted to a country where your brothers are expecting you with open arms.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And told them, that they are going from a country where they are not wanted to a country of liberty.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I had to, very early already in the speech-- it was only a two minute speech.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That they have to with absolute discipline is necessary on this trip.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On the train is where [INAUDIBLE] trip.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And anyone who will not be-- he break the discipline will be severely punished.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when I finished-- I hadn't planned it-- a girl, a 10-year-old girl started singing Hatikvah.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we sang Hatikvah and I, for a moment's hesitation, I fell in and sang Hatikvah, too.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this is they all stood at attention.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I stood and two of the guards next to me stood at attention, too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We sang Hatikvah.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then everyone on the chain of command said, blessing to you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They already said, blessing to you and left.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That was on the I think the 8th of June, 1938.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In the same evening, we discovered to our horror that the pass-- Turi, who had the passports to present on the Yugoslav border has forgotten the-- not Turi.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Somebody had forgotten the passports who was to pick them up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we traveled without passports for 24 hours in the next train with all the passports and brought them to the passports.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And next morning, I left for London.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before I have you go into London, I have just a couple of quick questions.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
